# Fakturoid API v3 Testing Credentials

# To run integration tests, you can use either Client Credentials (server-to-server) 
# OR a full OAuth Application with a Refresh Token.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 1: Client Credentials Flow (Easiest for local tests)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Go to Fakturoid -> Settings -> User account -> API (Client credentials flow)
FAKTUROID_CLIENT_ID="your-user-client-id"
FAKTUROID_CLIENT_SECRET="your-user-client-secret"
FAKTUROID_SLUG="your-account-slug" # e.g. 'applecorp'

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 2: OAuth Application Flow (Multi-tenant)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Go to Fakturoid -> Settings -> Connect other apps -> OAuth 2
# FAKTUROID_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID="your-oauth-app-client-id"
# FAKTUROID_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET="your-oauth-app-client-secret"
# FAKTUROID_REFRESH_TOKEN="a-valid-refresh-token"
# FAKTUROID_REDIRECT_URI="https://yourapp.com/callback"

# Note: If you provide ONLY FAKTUROID_CLIENT_ID and FAKTUROID_CLIENT_SECRET, 
# the test suite will automatically run in Client Credentials mode.
# If you provide FAKTUROID_REFRESH_TOKEN, it will run in OAuth mode.
